<paragraph blockId="32.[192,1440,1680,1928]" lastBlockId="33.[192,1441,217,338]" lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,1680,1704]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Definition.</emphasis>
A genus near 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1955" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1955" box="[511,759,1680,1704]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Joanna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[511,603,1680,1703]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Joanna</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[610,759,1680,1704]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans, 1955</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[774,828,1680,1704]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="joanna Evans, 1955" authorityName="joanna Evans" authorityYear="1955" box="[926,1265,1680,1704]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Joanna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="joanna">
<emphasis box="[926,1109,1680,1703]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Joanna joanna</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[1116,1265,1680,1704]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans, 1955</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Austin, 1997" authorityName="Austin" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Vinpeius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1332,1439,1680,1703]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Vinpeius</emphasis>
Austin, 1997
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[359,412,1712,1736]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">type</typeStatus>
and the only species 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1955" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1955" box="[663,1006,1712,1736]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pompeius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tinga">
<emphasis box="[663,851,1712,1735]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Pompeius tinga</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[856,1006,1712,1736]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans, 1955</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), and in same clade with 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubner, [1821]" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1821" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Niconiades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1305,1440,1712,1736]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Niconiades</emphasis>
Hübner, [1821]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[386,439,1744,1768]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubner, [1821]" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1821" box="[534,997,1744,1768]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Niconiades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthaphes">
<emphasis box="[534,810,1744,1768]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Niconiades xanthaphes</emphasis>
Hübner, [1821]
</taxonomicName>
), where it was placed previously (
<figureCitation captionStart-0="Figure 11" captionStart-1="Figure 12" captionStartId-0="29.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionStartId-1="31.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionTargetBox-0="[195,1438,214,1295]" captionTargetBox-1="[194,1440,214,1295]" captionTargetId-0="figure@29.[194,1442,213,1296]" captionTargetId-1="figure@31.[192,1440,213,1296]" captionTargetPageId-0="29" captionTargetPageId-1="31" captionText-0="Figure 11. Nuclear genome and Z chromosome trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." captionText-1="Figure 12. Mitochondrial genome and COI barcode trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677257" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677259" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3677257/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3677259/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Fig. 11–12</figureCitation>
). Indeed resembles some 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1821" box="[569,703,1776,1800]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Niconiades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[569,703,1776,1800]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Niconiades</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species due to the presence of large hyaline spots on hindwing and green scaling of the body, but genitalia (illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bell" box="[922,1043,1808,1832]" firstAuthor="Bell" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref26731" refString="Bell, E. L. 1959. Descriptions of some new species of neotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera, Rhopalocera). American Museum Novitates 1962: 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1959">Bell 1959</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 22 and 
<bibRefCitation author="Nicolay" box="[1194,1358,1808,1832]" firstAuthor="Nicolay" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref27965" refString="Nicolay, S. S. 1980. Descriptions of new Hesperiidae from Panama and Ecuador (Pyrginae and Hes- periinae). Bulletin of the Allyn Museum 59: 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1980">Nicolay 1980</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 8) quite distinctive and diagnostic: short uncus and tegumen, together not longer than valva height, uncus rounded and weakly bilobed caudad, saccus long, about half of vinculum length, penis narrowing caudad, valva broad, more than half of its length, ampulla transitions to harpe without a break, harpe projecting caudad as a broad straight tooth, indented before the tooth along ventral margin. (
<bibRefCitation author="Bell" box="[1149,1262,217,241]" firstAuthor="Bell" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref26731" refString="Bell, E. L. 1959. Descriptions of some new species of neotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera, Rhopalocera). American Museum Novitates 1962: 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1959">Bell 1959</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nicolay" box="[1272,1428,217,242]" firstAuthor="Nicolay" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref27965" refString="Nicolay, S. S. 1980. Descriptions of new Hesperiidae from Panama and Ecuador (Pyrginae and Hes- periinae). Bulletin of the Allyn Museum 59: 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1980">Nicolay 1980</bibRefCitation>
). In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly890.44.9:C94G, aly9673.13.1:C269G, aly3555.4.2:G923A, aly 
<date box="[476,598,282,306]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" value="1041-12-01">1041.12.1</date>
:T93T (not C), aly537.7.1:T984T (not C), aly 
<date box="[1131,1235,282,306]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" value="1038-08-01">1038.8.1</date>
:A1367A (not C), aly8857.2.1:G1234G (not A), aly1041.22.3:A377A (not G), aly517.17.2:G336G (not C).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="32" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="33.[192,1420,362,386]" box="[192,1420,362,386]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,347,362,386]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name, a masculine noun in the nominative singular, echoes the 
<typeStatus box="[1191,1244,362,386]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">type</typeStatus>
species name.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[192,1062,409,434]" box="[192,1062,409,434]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,432,409,433]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Species included.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[493,546,410,434]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">type</typeStatus>
species and 
<taxonomicName authority="Nicolay, 1980" authorityName="Nicolay" authorityYear="1980" box="[701,1059,409,434]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Thoon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maritza">
<emphasis box="[701,881,409,433]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Thoon maritza</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nicolay" box="[889,1059,410,434]" firstAuthor="Nicolay" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref27965" refString="Nicolay, S. S. 1980. Descriptions of new Hesperiidae from Panama and Ecuador (Pyrginae and Hes- periinae). Bulletin of the Allyn Museum 59: 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1980">Nicolay, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[192,823,458,482]" box="[192,823,458,482]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,380,458,482]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
Subtribe Moncina A. 
<bibRefCitation author="Warren, A. D. &amp; J. R. Ogawa &amp; A. V. Z. Brower" box="[647,819,458,482]" journalOrPublisher="Phylogenetic relationships of subfamilies and circumscription of tribes in the family Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera: Hesperioidea). Cladistics" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" pagination="642 - 676" part="24" refId="ref28580" refString="Warren, A. D., J. R. Ogawa, and A. V. Z. Brower. 2008. Phylogenetic relationships of subfamilies and circumscription of tribes in the family Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera: Hesperioidea). Cladistics 24 (5): 642 - 676." type="journal article" year="2008">Warren, 2008</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
